{"key":"post-12664004","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12664004</id>\n<content>If there's enough holes, there will be no condensation because there will be no heat differential across the surface.&amp;nbsp; Condensation is caused by a hotter surface on one side than the other.&amp;nbsp; It's not caused by humidity.&amp;nbsp; With a shotgun terrarium, there's enough air exchange through the holes that the temperature differential isn't enough to cause condensation.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>12662976</prev>\n<first>12658091</first>\n<last>12664004</last>\n<when>1275367674</when>\n<utime>06/01/10 07:47 AM</utime>\n</post>"}